tags.description: The School was established in the year 1959 by Dr. Kwame Nkrumah, and is located in Kumawu in the Ashanti Region.
tags.name: Tweneboa Kodua Senior High School

tags.description: Adanwomase shs was established as a private institution in 1972. The school started with a student population of thirty two (32) with six (6) teachers and nineteen (19) non teaching staff. The school was absorbed into the public system in 1977.
tags.name: Adanwomase Senior High School

tags.description: The school was established as a private institution by the Jamasi Presbyterian Church in 1968, with a student population of 80. It was absorbed into the public system in 1974. In 2008, the school was upgraded as a model school.
tags.name: Adu Gyamfi Senior High School

tags.description: Adventist Girls Senior High School is a full-fledged girls’ school popularly known as AHWEFO. The school is the only female second cycle institution in the Kwabre East District and the first of its kind among SDA institutions in Ghana and West Africa.
tags.name: Adventist Girls' Senior High School

tags.description: The school is situated on one kilometer square plot of land, at Agona Ashanti close to the Kumasi – Mampong truck road. It was established in 1963 by the SDA Mission.
tags.name: S.D.A. Senior High School, Agona

tags.description: The School is a mixed school and was established in 1965 as a Community School by the late J.C. Akosah to give access to Secondary education to the people of Mampong-Ashanti and its environs.
tags.name: Amaniampong Senior High School

tags.description: The school was founded by some illustrious elders of Antoa in 1969 as Adonten Akoten Secondary School. The school was renamed to it's current name when it was absorbed into the public school system in September 1971
tags.name: Antoa Senior High School

tags.description: Bankoman Senior High School was established in as a Community Day Secondary School to provide secondary education for the students of Banko and the surrounding villages.
tags.name: Bankoman Senior High School

tags.description: The school, located in the northern part of Bonwire, between Bamang and Amanpe junction, was established in 1991.
tags.name: Bonwire Senior High/Technical School

tags.description: Dadease Agric. Senior High school was established as a Community-Initiated Project in 1982 in the Sekyere Kumawu District of the Ashanti Region.
tags.name: Dadease Agric Senior High School

tags.description: It is one of the first 31 model schools set up by the Government in 1943.
tags.name: Effiduase Senior High School

tags.description: It is a Government Assisted academic-excellent school established on the 20th of October, 2008 to provide quality formal education to the ever growing youth of Beposo and its environs through affordable quality educational delivery and Islamic ethics
tags.name: Ghana Muslim Mission Senior High School

tags.description: Gyaama Pensan Senior High Technical School was established as a private institution in 1995 by one Dr. Kofi Asante Gyapong, the then chief of the town. He named the school after the then queenmother of the town.
tags.name: Gyaama Pensan Senior High/Technical School

tags.description: It was established in 1991 with a student population of 50, but can now boast of about 2000 students and has both day and boarding facilities.
tags.name: Kofi Adjei Senior High/Technical School

tags.description: Kofiase Adventist Senior High/Technical School was established on Monday 21st October, 2010 as a private day institution with 32 students, 20 of whom were boys and 12 girls.
tags.name: Kofiase Adventist Senior High/Technical School

tags.description: Konadu Yiadom Senior High School was established by the Asamang Community led by Asamanghene Barima Owusu Sekyere in 1975 as a Community School to provide co-education to the youth in Asamang
tags.name: Konadu Yiadom Catholic Senior High School

tags.description: Krobea Asante Technical Vocational Institute was established by Nana Susubribi Krobea Asante, the Omanhene of Asokore Traditional Area in, 1999, and commissioned by H E Janet Graham, the Canadian High Commissioner to Ghana.
tags.name: Krobea Asante Technical/Vocational Institute

tags.description: Nsutaman Catholic Senior High School was established in 1973 at Nsuta, the capital town of Sekyere Central District in the Ashanti Region
tags.name: Nsutaman Catholic Senior High School

tags.description: Okomfo Anokye Senior High School is a co-educational institution set-up as a Community School on 5th October, 1964. It was named Subri Secondary School after The Wiamoase stool.
tags.name: Okomfo Anokye Senior High School

tags.description: The school was established by the Kwamang Traditional Council in 2006 and handed over to the Presbyterian Church to manage. The school was later absorbed by the government in 2010.
tags.name: Presby Senior High/Technical School, Kwamang

tags.description: Agona Senior High Technical School was established in 1992 by the PNDC Government alongside 31 others in the Ashanti Region.
tags.name: Agona Senior High/Technical School

tags.description: Simms Senior High School was founded in 1977 as a Private School by Mr. Simms Kofi Mensah to provide education to the people of Kwabre. The School was absorbed into the Public system as one of the Government Assisted Secondary School in 1982.
tags.name: Simms Senior High School

tags.description: It is a co-educational Catholic Mission institution, which also serves as a Seminary for the Konongo Mampong diocese. The School, established in 1968, became a public school in 1989.

tags.description: The school is a female institution established 1946 by the sisters of the OHP - WHITBY in England.
tags.name: St. Monica's Senior High School

tags.description: T. I. Ahmadiyya Girls’ Senior High was established by the Ahmadiyya Muslim Mission, as a middle school in 1969. The school was later made to run as Secondary School.
tags.name: T. I. Ahmadiyya Girls' Senior High School

tags.description: Tijjaniya Senior High School located at Asokore, was established in 2009
tags.name: Tijjaniya Senior High School

tags.description: The school can be found off the main road between Tafo and Mamponten. Its exact location is Asenua and it is duly registered under Kumasi Metro.
tags.name: Komfo Anokye Senior High School

tags.description: The school was established by a native of the town, Mr. Akwasi Acheampong who had the ambition of ensuring quality, accessible and affordable education within the locality.
tags.name: Mountain High Senior High School

tags.description: Oduko Boatemaa Senior High is a private school at Asante Mampong. It offers General Art, Business, Home Economics and Visual Art. It has state of the art facilities and can cater for four hundred and fifty (450) students.
tags.name: Oduko Boatemaa Senior High School
